From: Takeshi Kihara <takeshi.kihara.df@renesas.com>
Date: Tue, 7 Feb 2017 16:37:06 +0900
Subject: [PATCH 1753/2066] arm64: dts: r8a7795-salvator-x: Add Media Clock
 Recovery Handler device node

This patch adds Media Clock Recovery Handler device node for Salvator-X
board on R8A7795 ES2.0 SoC.

Signed-off-by: Takeshi Kihara <takeshi.kihara.df@renesas.com>
[zou:Original patch taken from
git://git.kernel.org/pub/scm/linux/kernel/git/horms/renesas-bsp.git
 v4.9/rcar-3.5.1]
Signed-off-by: zou cao <cao.zou@windriver.com>
---
 arch/arm64/boot/dts/renesas/r8a7795-salvator-x.dts |    9 +++++++++
 1 files changed, 9 insertions(+), 0 deletions(-)

diff --git a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/renesas/r8a7795-salvator-x.dts b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/renesas/r8a7795-salvator-x.dts
index 9d4946fe..d864a1b 100644
--- a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/renesas/r8a7795-salvator-x.dts
+++ b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/renesas/r8a7795-salvator-x.dts
@@ -114,6 +114,15 @@
 		compatible = "renesas,mmngrbuf";
 	};
 
+	avb-mch {
+		compatible = "renesas,avb-mch-gen3";
+		reg =	<0 0xec5a0100 0 0x100>;  /* ADG_AVB */
+		reg-name = "adg_avb";
+
+		clocks = <&cpg CPG_MOD 922>;
+		clock-names = "adg";
+	};
+
 	x12_clk: x12_clk {
 		compatible = "fixed-clock";
 		#clock-cells = <0>;
